data.name: chkAdvancedSearch.ToolTip
data.value:
If unchecked (default), search only on the AlbumArtistTitle data (faster).
If checked, perform an advanced search of the data (more inclusive, and slower).
This checkbox is interactive, i.e. you may see different results when it is toggled if a search criterion has been entered.
Give column filtering a try, if Search doesn't find what you are looking for. Click on a column header filter icon.

data.name: cmsActions.ToolTipText
data.value:
NOTE: Multiple selections can be made for 'Enable/Disable Songs', 'Delete Songs' and 'Backup Songs'.
For safety, the column 'Select' checkbox must be checked to perform these three File IO related 'Actions'.

data.name: tsmiRepairsMastery.ToolTipText
data.value:
Mastery 100% Bug is repaired by default regardless of other selected options.
Once the Mastery Bug is repaired the CDLC is considered to be 'Remastered'.
NOTE: If user fails to specify sub options for this repair then stats are preserved by default, i.e. the user will be stuck at 100% mastery.

data.name: tsmiRepairsPreserveStats.ToolTipText
data.value:
If checked, preserves in-game stats.
If unchecked, reset the song stats and reduce the risk of in-game hangs.
NOTE: If you choose to preserve stats then make sure only one version of the CDLC is in the 'dlc' folder at a time otherwise in-game hangs will happen.

data.name: tsmiRepairsUsingOrg.ToolTipText
data.value:
Developers do not recommend use of this option.
If selected, only files from the (org) folder are used for the selected repair options. This option may not be combined with the "Process Downloads Folder" button

data.name: tsmiDLFolderProcess.ToolTipText
data.value:
Process new CDLC from downloads folder and move them to 'dlc/downloads' folder. When selected, only the files in the downloads folder are processed/repaired.
NOTE: The CDLC downloads folder location may be reset from the 'Settings' tab menu.

data.name: tsmiDLFolderMonitor.ToolTipText
data.value:
If checked, automatically monitor the downloads folder for new CDLC then process/repair any new CDLC and move them to 'dlc/downloads' folder.
Note: Must be unchecked before using the 'Run Selected Repair Options'.
Make a donation at https://goo.gl/iTPfRU and show your support for this feature or just use the 'Click to Donate' button.

data.name: tsmiCustomTitleTagPrefix.ToolTipText
data.value:
If this option is selected, Custom Title Tag will be used as a prefix ... For example, if you tag a song named 'Heavy Rain' with tag 'Tagio', it will end up as, 'Tagio Heavy Rain'.
Conversely, select to remove a tag that was used as a prefix.

data.name: tsmiCustomTitleTagSuffix.ToolTipText
data.value:
If this option is selected, Custom Title Tag will be used as a suffix ... For example, if you tag a song named 'Heavy Rain' with tag 'Tagio', it will end up as, 'Heavy Rain Tagio'.
Conversely, select to remove a tag that was used as a suffix.

data.name: tsmiCustomTitleTag.ToolTipText
data.value:
Add a Custom Title Tag to any selected song ... As an example, for the song 'My Song', you can add the tag 'B Std' as a prefix, and it will end up as 'B Std My Song'.
NOTE: in order to remove a tag, enter the tag in the 'Enter Title Tag' input box as you did when you added it, and then press 'Remove Tag'.

data.name: tsmiModsPitchShifter.ToolTipText
data.value:
Add additional options to Pitch Shifter if desired with check boxes before pressing Pitch Shifter.
NOTE: Pitch shifting is currently derived from Low E (String0) tuning and the arrangement will be accordingly changed to E Standard or Drop D.

data.name: tsmiModsPreserveStats.ToolTipText
data.value:
If checked, preserves in-game stats.
If unchecked, reset the song stats and reduce the risk of in-game hangs.
NOTE: If you choose to preserve stats then make sure only one version of the CDLC is in the 'dlc' folder at a time otherwise in-game hangs will happen.

data.name: tsmiAutoAdjustVolume.ToolTipText
data.value:
SELECT some CDLC then CLICK to run ...
User adjustable CDLC volume variables for POC testing only.
Please report any combinations that produce CDLC volumes comparable with ODLC to Developers.
These variables will be locked after POC testing is completed in order to produce consistent results.
HINT: reset all defaults in Settings menu

data.name: tsmiFilesOrganize.ToolTipText
data.value:
Quickly organize CDLC files into ArtistName subfolders and rename CDLC with 'ArtistName_SongName_Vers#_p.psarc'
WARNING ------------ You may not want to use this feature if you have created custom setlists with Setlist Manager and/or have renamed any songs with Renamer. All selected songs will be rename and moved to ArtistName subfolders.
On the flip side, this feature can be used to quickly create setlists by ArtistName.

data.name: tsmiFilesUnorganize.ToolTipText
data.value:
Restore CDLC files back to the master 'dlc' and 'dlc/cdlc' folders and removes empty ArtistName subfolders.
WARNING ------------ This will remove any custom setlists that were created using Setlist Manager. Songs are not renamed during restore operations.
